&lt;h3 id=&#34;polars&#34;&gt;Polars&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;pip3 install polars
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4 id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;Introduction&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/ritchie46/polars/blob/master/README.md&#34;&gt;Ref&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Polars is a blazingly ⚡ fast DataFrames library implemented in Rust. Its memory model uses Apache Arrow  🏹 as backend.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It currently consists of an &lt;strong&gt;eager API&lt;/strong&gt; similar to pandas and a &lt;strong&gt;lazy API&lt;/strong&gt; that is somewhat similar to spark.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
